1:#!/usr/bin/env python3
2:"""Assemble the per-symbol 15m research dataset from raw Binance Vision zips.
3:
4:ALL timestamp/alignment conventions live HERE and nowhere else:
5:- canonical candle close = open_time + 15m; the archive's close_time field (open+15m-1ms) is never read
6:- every timestamp is normalized to tz-aware UTC at load; metrics CSVs carry naive datetime strings
7:  and are parsed with utc=True explicitly (a KST-local parse would shift OI 9h into the future)
8:- kline epoch columns are milliseconds until 2025-01 and MICROSECONDS after; unit is detected
9:  per file by magnitude
10:- OI joined with merge_asof(direction="backward", tolerance=25min); the snapshot exactly at close
11:  IS included; beyond tolerance the candle has no OI (degrade path), never a stale fill
12:- klines are reindexed to a complete 15m UTC grid; missing bars flagged, never interpolated
13:- funding is snapped to the 8h UTC grid (assert offset < 60s) and applied to candles closing
14:  at-or-after the event (backward merge)
