1:#!/usr/bin/env python3
2:"""Free-data axis candidates, tested on the existing harness. Encodings are PRE-REGISTERED
3:in NOTES.md before any result was seen — no tuning on outcome.
4:
5:  A taker: taker buy/sell vol ratio 30d past-only percentile; >=0.75 votes TREND_UP,
6:           <=0.25 votes TREND_DOWN (replaces the OI fuel axis; reference = B2)
7:  B lsr:   top-trader long/short ratio, k-bar relative change with rolling-q25 deadzone;
8:           rising votes UP, falling votes DOWN (reference = B2)
9:  C dvol:  Deribit DVOL (implied vol) blended into the volatility axis as a third
10:           percentile; fuel stays standard OI (reference = standard F)
11:
12:Metric per variant: pooled enter-TREND lead vs B1; marginal = observed raw median diff vs
13:the reference; paired month-cluster CI; circular time-shift null (200) of the SOURCE series.
14:
15:Usage: python alt_axes.py [BTCUSDT] [--nulls 200]
16:"""
