Static audit of current code and saved outputs; Python execution was blocked by the read-only environment.

1. High — The “4–6 candles later” result is conditional on a minority of baseline episodes. Only 47.1% of UP and 41.6% of DOWN episodes match; 1,823 of 3,270 baseline episodes are missed. The matcher greedily maximizes overlap rather than globally maximizing match cardinality, and accepts 25% of the shorter interval, permitting weak correspondences ([leadlag.py:62](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/leadlag.py:62), [leadlag.py:71](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/leadlag.py:71)). The defensible claim is: “among jointly detected episodes, F starts 4–6 bars later.”

2. High — “Near-zero false alarms” is denominator-driven. False episodes are divided by all 154,560 candles ([leadlag.py:115](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/leadlag.py:115)). Relative to fused episodes, 202/1,649 = 12.2% are unmatched—materially different from “near zero.” The −32.6% churn claim itself is numerically correct.

3. Medium — Bootstrap uncertainty is understated. Months are resampled after matching; episodes and matches are not reconstructed ([leadlag.py:152](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/leadlag.py:152)). Cross-month dependence and matching-selection uncertainty are omitted. The “paired” F−B2 bootstrap uses the same months but separately matched event populations, not episode-paired differences ([leadlag.py:168](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/leadlag.py:168)). Moving multi-month blocks with full rematching would be stronger.

4. High — `p=1.0` does not establish “indistinguishable” or equivalence. It is a one-sided exceedance test with discrete, heavily tied medians ([run_all.py:266](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/run_all.py:266)). It supports “no evidence of superior timing,” not “no effect.” The OI result is plausibly structural because random OI still gates votes using actual price direction, but an equivalence margin was never tested.

5. Medium — Circular shifts are not an exact randomization null under nonstationarity. Shifts are restricted to 2–90 days ([run_all.py:235](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/run_all.py:235)); slow DVOL/positioning regimes can remain aligned. Null runs also move missingness and change the evaluation mask ([run_all.py:245](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/run_all.py:245), [run_all.py:254](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/run_all.py:254)). Alternative-axis shifts additionally omit seam masking ([alt_axes.py:150](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/alt_axes.py:150)). False negatives therefore remain possible.

6. Medium — Core rolling features are causal, but test claims are overstated. The test can skip completely without archives, checks only seven cut points, and the canary covers only OI ([test_no_lookahead.py:34](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/tests/test_no_lookahead.py:34), [test_no_lookahead.py:96](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/tests/test_no_lookahead.py:96)). Float comparison retains NumPy’s default relative tolerance, so it is not exact `atol=1e-12` ([test_no_lookahead.py:87](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/tests/test_no_lookahead.py:87)). Funding timestamps are rounded, potentially backdating a slightly late event by up to 60 seconds ([build_dataset.py:175](C:/Users/user/Desktop/Auto-trade-system/research/regime/build_dataset.py:175)).

